The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Lashkar kingpin killed
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Lashkar kingpin killed
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                               
	Srinagar, May 28: A top Lashkar commander accused of masterminding the 2006 Kulhind massacre of 19 people was today killed near Jammu.        
	Shabir Ahmed Ittoo alias Abu Yasir and Samreena Bano, believed to be his wife, were killed in Doda districts Gunda Khandepura village in a joint operation by the army and police. Both were Doda residents.         
	Nineteen Hindus had been killed in the August 2006 attack in Kulhind, also in Doda.        
	Defence spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel S.D. Goswami said the Rashtriya Rifles and the police launched todays operation after a tip-off about their presence in the village. Both Shabir and his wife were killed in the hideout.        
	Doda police chief Manohar Singh said while Shabir was not directly involved and had not participated in the massacre, he was the Lashkar commander at the time and had masterminded the attack.                                                                                                                                                                                        
